A weathered craftsman's hands guiding younger hands shaping clay on a pottery wheel, captured in warm golden afternoon light streaming through a dusty workshop window, photorealistic style with shallow depth of field, the older hands showing decades of calluses and clay stains while gently positioning the apprentice's fingers, spinning wet clay rising between them, wood shavings and finished ceramic vessels blurred in the background, intimate overhead angle emphasizing the transfer of knowledge through touch, rich earth tones of terracotta, amber, and deep brown dominating the palette, dust particles floating in the light beams creating an almost sacred atmosphere of tradition and craft being passed between generations.
